President Donald J. Trump will send a Presidential Delegation to Bangkok, Thailand to attend the Royal Cremation Ceremony of the late King Bhumibol Adulyadej on October 26, 2017. Secretary of Defense James Mattis will lead the delegation as the President's Special Envoy, joined by United States Ambassador to Thailand Glyn Davies. President Trump offers condolences on behalf of the American people and recognizes King Bhumibol Adulyadej as a champion of the Thai people and the United States-Thailand alliance. The President acknowledges the late King's innovative work, diplomacy, and 70 years of selfless service, ensuring that his legacy will endure for generations to come.